Qatar have unveiled the design for their fifth World Cup stadium  . 
  The Al Rayyan Stadium is inspired by sand dunes and will be built in 'the gateway to the desert' The 40,000-seater ground is expected to host matches up to the quarter-final stage of the 2022 tournament in Qatar . 
  The design has been produced by UK-based architecture firms Ramboll and Pattern  . 
  The stadium will feature air conditioning for the comfort of players and fans  . 
  The ground is set to be completed in early 2019 . 
 